This paper is primarily focused on constructing a novel face image dataset with a balanced race composition, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the evaluation of the dataset using existing face attribute datasets, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Flickr dataset for collecting images, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential biases in existing face datasets, which is relevant to the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
